            <PositionHistory positionType="contract">
               <Title>Senior Consultant</Title>
               <OrganizationName>Metis Program, US Air Force</OrganizationName>
               <Description>
                  <p>The United States Air Force needed a search and visualization capability to access a very large repository of sensitive information, which is one-of-a-kind in its classified content. The project moved all of the information from paper and microfiche to digital, while at the same time providing a state-of-the-art MarkLogic-based search and visualization capability. The project used several other open source and COTS products in its final solution.</p>
                  <p>Outcomes of the project included:</p>
                  <ul>
                     <li> An automated ingestion process
                that could ingest hundreds of documents</li>
                     <li> A powerful search
                capability</li>
                     <li> A temporal and spatial search and
                visualization capability</li>
                     <li> A customized administration tool
                to help government quality control personnel</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>The final product reduced search time from months to minutes for requests for data. Eric was a lead developer on this project.</p>
               </Description>
               <StartDate>1000-01-01</StartDate>
            </PositionHistory>
            <PositionHistory positionType="contract">
               <Title>Senior Consultant</Title>
               <OrganizationName>Materials Data Evaluation System, US Air Force</OrganizationName>
               <Description>
                  <p>The US Air Force needed a web-based collaborative simulation and modeling capability, which also provided a workflow-like reporting functionality.</p>
                  <p>Eric designed, developed and tested various client and web-based applications in support of modeling and simulation, and reporting requirements. A few of the applications included a map for displaying weather and concentration data, a collaborative report creation tool, a report publishing tool that interfaced with an external system, and a data format conversion tool.</p>
               </Description>
               <StartDate>1000-01-01</StartDate>
